    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-16T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-16T03:00:00-05:00" n="642"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/4703: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tunis</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Heisler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tunis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-16T10:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 16, 1940—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 16—7:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Officially informed a commission consisting of seven Italian naval officers
                    arrived at Bizerte July 7 and is still there owing to suspension armistice terms
                    regarding disarmament French Mediterranean ports.</p>
                <p>British Consular Corps left Tunis July 10 but French permission for this
                    Consulate to represent British interests not yet received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Heisler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
